{
  "video_id": "jQ6smN3lcnY",
  "title": "Episode 1.1: What is Torts? And what Torts is not.",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 2635.0,
      "end_time": 4436.0,
      "text": ">> \"What is Torts?"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 4437.0,
      "end_time": 6806.0,
      "text": "\"And what Torts is not.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 6806.0,
      "end_time": 10577.0,
      "text": "A tort is a wrongful act, other than a breach of contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 10577.0,
      "end_time": 13613.0,
      "text": "that results in injury to another party&#39;s person,"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 13613.0,
      "end_time": 16820.0,
      "text": "property, dignity, or reputation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 16820.0,
      "end_time": 19850.0,
      "text": "and which is recognized by statute or common law"
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 19850.0,
      "end_time": 21721.0,
      "text": "as a legitimate basis for liability."
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 21721.0,
      "end_time": 25859.0,
      "text": "In other words, torts is the law of civil wrongs."
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 25859.0,
      "end_time": 29262.0,
      "text": "Now, this definition raises some important distinctions"
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 29262.0,
      "end_time": 31998.0,
      "text": "that are worth addressing before we move on."
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 31998.0,
      "end_time": 35680.0,
      "text": "Civil or criminal cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 35680.0,
      "end_time": 38738.0,
      "text": "common law or statutory law,"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 38738.0,
      "end_time": 41574.0,
      "text": "tort or contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 41574.0,
      "end_time": 43876.0,
      "text": "Let&#39;s go through these one by one."
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 43877.0,
      "end_time": 46646.0,
      "text": "Civil or criminal cases."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 46646.0,
      "end_time": 48715.0,
      "text": "Like contracts and property,"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 48715.0,
      "end_time": 53253.0,
      "text": "tort law provides for civil rather than criminal liability."
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 53253.0,
      "end_time": 55121.0,
      "text": "There are some crucial distinctions here"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 55121.0,
      "end_time": 58892.0,
      "text": "having to do with, one, who the parties are--"
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 58892.0,
      "end_time": 62162.0,
      "text": "plaintiff as opposed to prosecutor."
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 62162.0,
      "end_time": 65765.0,
      "text": "Two, what the possible outcomes are--"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 65765.0,
      "end_time": 68935.0,
      "text": "liable as opposed to guilty."
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68935.0,
      "end_time": 72439.0,
      "text": "Three, the applicable standard of proof--"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 72439.0,
      "end_time": 77110.0,
      "text": "preponderance as opposed to beyond a reasonable doubt."
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 77110.0,
      "end_time": 80780.0,
      "text": "Four, the consequences for the defendant--"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 80780.0,
      "end_time": 84851.0,
      "text": "civil damages as opposed to criminal penalties."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 84851.0,
      "end_time": 88922.0,
      "text": "And five, the procedural rules that apply--"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 88922.0,
      "end_time": 92692.0,
      "text": "civil procedure as opposed to criminal procedure."
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 92692.0,
      "end_time": 97130.0,
      "text": "First, torts are disputes between private parties."
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 97130.0,
      "end_time": 99999.0,
      "text": "In a tort action, the injured plaintiff brings suit"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 99999.0,
      "end_time": 103360.0,
      "text": "against the defendant for damages,"
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 103360.0,
      "end_time": 106172.0,
      "text": "whereas in a criminal action, the prosecutor,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 106172.0,
      "end_time": 107941.0,
      "text": "acting on behalf of the government,"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 107941.0,
      "end_time": 110777.0,
      "text": "charges the defendant with a crime."
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 110777.0,
      "end_time": 114380.0,
      "text": "The injuries on which a claim of tort liability is based"
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 114380.0,
      "end_time": 117317.0,
      "text": "might also form the basis of a criminal action."
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 117317.0,
      "end_time": 119219.0,
      "text": "But the two cases would be initiated"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 119219.0,
      "end_time": 122589.0,
      "text": "by different parties, and would proceed separately."
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 122589.0,
      "end_time": 125158.0,
      "text": "For example, O.J. Simpson"
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 125158.0,
      "end_time": 128161.0,
      "text": "was tried by a prosecutor on two counts of murder--"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 128161.0,
      "end_time": 130797.0,
      "text": "People of the State of California v. Simpson--"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 130797.0,
      "end_time": 135134.0,
      "text": "and acquitted... AKA, found not guilty."
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 135134.0,
      "end_time": 138704.0,
      "text": "He was also sued by the families of Nicole Brown Simpson"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 138705.0,
      "end_time": 141241.0,
      "text": "and Ron Goldman for wrongful death--"
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 141241.0,
      "end_time": 145110.0,
      "text": "Goldman v. Simpson-- and found liable."
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 145110.0,
      "end_time": 148147.0,
      "text": "In some, criminal cases are the people"
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 148147.0,
      "end_time": 150783.0,
      "text": "represented by the prosecutor v. defendant,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 150783.0,
      "end_time": 154686.0,
      "text": "and tort suits are plaintiff v. defendant."
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 154687.0,
      "end_time": 157657.0,
      "text": "Second, notice that the possible outcomes"
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 157657.0,
      "end_time": 159259.0,
      "text": "are also different."
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 159259.0,
      "end_time": 161126.0,
      "text": "In criminal cases, the defendant"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 161127.0,
      "end_time": 163396.0,
      "text": "is found guilty or not guilty."
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 163396.0,
      "end_time": 168233.0,
      "text": "In tort suits, the defendant is liable or not liable."
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 168234.0,
      "end_time": 171738.0,
      "text": "Third, the standard of proof is different."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 171738.0,
      "end_time": 174140.0,
      "text": "In a criminal case, the standard of proof"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 174140.0,
      "end_time": 177309.0,
      "text": "is beyond a reasonable doubt,"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 177310.0,
      "end_time": 178478.0,
      "text": "but in a civil case,"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 178478.0,
      "end_time": 181748.0,
      "text": "the standard of proof, with a few narrow exceptions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 181748.0,
      "end_time": 184851.0,
      "text": "is a preponderance of the evidence."
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 184851.0,
      "end_time": 187453.0,
      "text": "The preponderance standard has been interpreted"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 187453.0,
      "end_time": 190490.0,
      "text": "to mean that the finder of fact must be convinced"
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 190490.0,
      "end_time": 192592.0,
      "text": "that the plaintiff&#39;s assertions"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 192592.0,
      "end_time": 196290.0,
      "text": "are more likely than not accurate."
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 196290.0,
      "end_time": 200533.0,
      "text": "Some courts have quantified this as more than 50% likely."
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 200533.0,
      "end_time": 202969.0,
      "text": "The difference between the civil and criminal"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 202969.0,
      "end_time": 205672.0,
      "text": "standard of proof might explain the divergence"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 205672.0,
      "end_time": 210343.0,
      "text": "between the criminal and civil Simpson cases."
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 210343.0,
      "end_time": 214647.0,
      "text": "Fourth, the consequences for the defendant are different."
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 214647.0,
      "end_time": 217830.0,
      "text": "If a criminal defendant is found guilty,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 217830.0,
      "end_time": 219218.0,
      "text": "the penalties might include death,"
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 219218.0,
      "end_time": 221954.0,
      "text": "imprisonment, or criminal fines."
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 221955.0,
      "end_time": 225525.0,
      "text": "In a tort suit, if the defendant is found liable,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 225525.0,
      "end_time": 227493.0,
      "text": "the most common remedy is that the court"
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 227493.0,
      "end_time": 230263.0,
      "text": "will order the defendant to pay damages."
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 230263.0,
      "end_time": 233766.0,
      "text": "Though, in some cases, equitable relief may be available,"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 233766.0,
      "end_time": 235969.0,
      "text": "meaning that the court can issue an injunction,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 235969.0,
      "end_time": 240506.0,
      "text": "ordering the defendant to take or refrain from certain actions."
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 240506.0,
      "end_time": 243176.0,
      "text": "Typically, criminal fines are paid"
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 243176.0,
      "end_time": 245445.0,
      "text": "by the dependent to the government."
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 245445.0,
      "end_time": 249983.0,
      "text": "Civil damages are paid by the defendant to the plaintiff."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 249983.0,
      "end_time": 253186.0,
      "text": "Finally, the procedural rules are also different"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 253186.0,
      "end_time": 255955.0,
      "text": "for civil as opposed to criminal cases,"
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 255955.0,
      "end_time": 260226.0,
      "text": "meaning civil procedure as opposed to criminal procedure."
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 261594.0,
      "end_time": 264664.0,
      "text": "There are two types of law that can form the basis"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 264664.0,
      "end_time": 269936.0,
      "text": "of civil liability-- common law or statutory law."
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 269936.0,
      "end_time": 272638.0,
      "text": "When you think of law, you probably think"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 272639.0,
      "end_time": 275541.0,
      "text": "of statutes passed by legislatures--"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 275541.0,
      "end_time": 276943.0,
      "text": "the U.S. Congress,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 276943.0,
      "end_time": 279579.0,
      "text": "the State Legislature, or the City Council--"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 279579.0,
      "end_time": 282148.0,
      "text": "and signed into law by executives--"
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 282148.0,
      "end_time": 285752.0,
      "text": "the President, Governor, or Mayor."
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 285752.0,
      "end_time": 290456.0,
      "text": "Sometimes, these statues include private causes of action,"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 290456.0,
      "end_time": 293159.0,
      "text": "meaning that the statute includes a provision"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 293159.0,
      "end_time": 295561.0,
      "text": "allowing private parties to sue each other"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 295561.0,
      "end_time": 298864.0,
      "text": "to enforce the rights recognized in that statute."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 298865.0,
      "end_time": 301467.0,
      "text": "For example, employment discrimination law"
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 301467.0,
      "end_time": 304437.0,
      "text": "is now dictated largely by statutes."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 304437.0,
      "end_time": 308107.0,
      "text": "Those statutes typically create private causes of action,"
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 308107.0,
      "end_time": 310760.0,
      "text": "allowing employees who believe"
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 310760.0,
      "end_time": 312145.0,
      "text": "that they have been discriminated against"
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 312145.0,
      "end_time": 315281.0,
      "text": "to sue their employers for violating the law."
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 315281.0,
      "end_time": 317750.0,
      "text": "The rules and standards that a court would use"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 317750.0,
      "end_time": 319252.0,
      "text": "to adjudicate such a dispute"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 319252.0,
      "end_time": 322121.0,
      "text": "are derived from the statute itself."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 322121.0,
      "end_time": 326920.0,
      "text": "Like contracts and property, tort law is primarily"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 326920.0,
      "end_time": 327727.0,
      "text": "a common law subject,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 327727.0,
      "end_time": 330996.0,
      "text": "meaning that it is primarily judge-made"
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 330997.0,
      "end_time": 333332.0,
      "text": "rather than legislature-made."
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 334400.0,
      "end_time": 336369.0,
      "text": "Most of tort law has evolved"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 336369.0,
      "end_time": 339372.0,
      "text": "through thousands upon thousands of court decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 339372.0,
      "end_time": 342642.0,
      "text": "arising out of individual disputes."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 342642.0,
      "end_time": 345578.0,
      "text": "The holdings of these individual court decisions"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 345578.0,
      "end_time": 348214.0,
      "text": "are treated as precedents, which are then applied"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 348214.0,
      "end_time": 352285.0,
      "text": "to future disputes that arise within the same jurisdiction."
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 352285.0,
      "end_time": 355421.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s worth noting that, particularly in torts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 355421.0,
      "end_time": 357857.0,
      "text": "the common law and statutory law"
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 357857.0,
      "end_time": 361627.0,
      "text": "interact with each other in a few important ways."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 361627.0,
      "end_time": 364564.0,
      "text": "First, in many jurisdictions,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 364564.0,
      "end_time": 368534.0,
      "text": "at least part of the common law of torts-- created by judges--"
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 368534.0,
      "end_time": 371300.0,
      "text": "has been codified into statutory law"
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 371300.0,
      "end_time": 373873.0,
      "text": "at some point by the legislature."
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 373873.0,
      "end_time": 377409.0,
      "text": "Often the legislature effectively ratifies the rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 377410.0,
      "end_time": 379946.0,
      "text": "that judges have developed over time."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 379946.0,
      "end_time": 383182.0,
      "text": "In the absence of this kind of ratification,"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 383182.0,
      "end_time": 385985.0,
      "text": "judge-made rules are still valid..."
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 385985.0,
      "end_time": 388821.0,
      "text": "but when the legislature has codified an area"
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 388821.0,
      "end_time": 391858.0,
      "text": "of common law, attorneys and judges must look"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 391858.0,
      "end_time": 394327.0,
      "text": "to the relevant statute first,"
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 394327.0,
      "end_time": 396562.0,
      "text": "not merely to the applicable precedents"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 396562.0,
      "end_time": 399232.0,
      "text": "or restatement sections."
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 399232.0,
      "end_time": 402301.0,
      "text": "Second, the legislature has authority,"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 402301.0,
      "end_time": 404736.0,
      "text": "pursuant to constitutional restraints,"
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 404737.0,
      "end_time": 406439.0,
      "text": "to reject the rules and standards"
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 406439.0,
      "end_time": 408908.0,
      "text": "adopted by the judiciary."
    },
    {
      "index": 135,
      "start_time": 408908.0,
      "end_time": 411611.0,
      "text": "You can think of the judiciary and the legislature"
    },
    {
      "index": 136,
      "start_time": 411611.0,
      "end_time": 414413.0,
      "text": "as being in conversation with each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 137,
      "start_time": 414413.0,
      "end_time": 417250.0,
      "text": "If the judiciary recognizes a common law rule"
    },
    {
      "index": 138,
      "start_time": 417250.0,
      "end_time": 419452.0,
      "text": "that the legislature doesn&#39;t like,"
    },
    {
      "index": 139,
      "start_time": 419452.0,
      "end_time": 422288.0,
      "text": "the legislature is free to pass a statute"
    },
    {
      "index": 140,
      "start_time": 422288.0,
      "end_time": 423956.0,
      "text": "adopting a different rule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 141,
      "start_time": 423956.0,
      "end_time": 427527.0,
      "text": "and judges are then bound by that legislative pronouncement"
    },
    {
      "index": 142,
      "start_time": 427527.0,
      "end_time": 429462.0,
      "text": "in future cases."
    },
    {
      "index": 143,
      "start_time": 429462.0,
      "end_time": 432231.0,
      "text": "The common law cause of action, or rule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 144,
      "start_time": 432231.0,
      "end_time": 435835.0,
      "text": "is said to have been \"preempted by the legislature.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 145,
      "start_time": 435835.0,
      "end_time": 439370.0,
      "text": "Third, if the legislature has passed a statute"
    },
    {
      "index": 146,
      "start_time": 439380.0,
      "end_time": 441240.0,
      "text": "that is relevant to a tort dispute,"
    },
    {
      "index": 147,
      "start_time": 441240.0,
      "end_time": 444977.0,
      "text": "but does not actually preempt the common law cause of action,"
    },
    {
      "index": 148,
      "start_time": 444977.0,
      "end_time": 447246.0,
      "text": "the courts might take that legislative pronouncement"
    },
    {
      "index": 149,
      "start_time": 447246.0,
      "end_time": 451820.0,
      "text": "into account, particularly when applying common law rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 150,
      "start_time": 451830.0,
      "end_time": 454120.0,
      "text": "that implicate policy considerations."
    },
    {
      "index": 151,
      "start_time": 454120.0,
      "end_time": 456489.0,
      "text": "Tort or contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 152,
      "start_time": 456489.0,
      "end_time": 459392.0,
      "text": "Within civil common law liability,"
    },
    {
      "index": 153,
      "start_time": 459392.0,
      "end_time": 461194.0,
      "text": "there is also an important distinction"
    },
    {
      "index": 154,
      "start_time": 461194.0,
      "end_time": 465398.0,
      "text": "between tort liability and contract liability."
    },
    {
      "index": 155,
      "start_time": 465398.0,
      "end_time": 470703.0,
      "text": "Remember, the definition of tort excludes breaches of contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 156,
      "start_time": 470703.0,
      "end_time": 472905.0,
      "text": "One useful way of thinking about the distinction"
    },
    {
      "index": 157,
      "start_time": 472905.0,
      "end_time": 476208.0,
      "text": "between torts and contracts is that contract law"
    },
    {
      "index": 158,
      "start_time": 476209.0,
      "end_time": 480120.0,
      "text": "governs the creation and enforcement of agreements,"
    },
    {
      "index": 159,
      "start_time": 480120.0,
      "end_time": 482582.0,
      "text": "where as tort law dictates the relationships"
    },
    {
      "index": 160,
      "start_time": 482582.0,
      "end_time": 485510.0,
      "text": "between parties who have not previously agreed"
    },
    {
      "index": 161,
      "start_time": 485510.0,
      "end_time": 486818.0,
      "text": "to a set of rules that will govern"
    },
    {
      "index": 162,
      "start_time": 486819.0,
      "end_time": 488955.0,
      "text": "their dealings with each other."
    },
    {
      "index": 163,
      "start_time": 488955.0,
      "end_time": 492910.0,
      "text": "For example, I bump into you on the sidewalk,"
    },
    {
      "index": 164,
      "start_time": 492910.0,
      "end_time": 494160.0,
      "text": "knocking you into oncoming traffic"
    },
    {
      "index": 165,
      "start_time": 494160.0,
      "end_time": 496429.0,
      "text": "causing you various injuries."
    },
    {
      "index": 166,
      "start_time": 496429.0,
      "end_time": 499998.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ve never met before, so we haven&#39;t had an opportunity"
    },
    {
      "index": 167,
      "start_time": 499999.0,
      "end_time": 502680.0,
      "text": "to agree to the rules that will dictate"
    },
    {
      "index": 168,
      "start_time": 502680.0,
      "end_time": 505438.0,
      "text": "whether I must compensate you for those injuries."
    },
    {
      "index": 169,
      "start_time": 505438.0,
      "end_time": 508274.0,
      "text": "Tort law provides a set of default rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 170,
      "start_time": 508274.0,
      "end_time": 511100.0,
      "text": "which govern our interactions."
    },
    {
      "index": 171,
      "start_time": 511100.0,
      "end_time": 514380.0,
      "text": "In other situations, two parties have had the opportunity"
    },
    {
      "index": 172,
      "start_time": 514380.0,
      "end_time": 517150.0,
      "text": "to agree to a set of obligations between them"
    },
    {
      "index": 173,
      "start_time": 517150.0,
      "end_time": 518483.0,
      "text": "that will govern their dealings,"
    },
    {
      "index": 174,
      "start_time": 518484.00000000006,
      "end_time": 520953.00000000006,
      "text": "or at least some aspect of those dealings."
    },
    {
      "index": 175,
      "start_time": 520953.0,
      "end_time": 522954.0,
      "text": "If I fail to fulfill an obligation"
    },
    {
      "index": 176,
      "start_time": 522955.00000000006,
      "end_time": 524557.0,
      "text": "that I have agreed to,"
    },
    {
      "index": 177,
      "start_time": 524557.0,
      "end_time": 527894.0,
      "text": "then I might be liable for breach of contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 178,
      "start_time": 527894.0,
      "end_time": 530429.0,
      "text": "For example, imagine you and I have entered"
    },
    {
      "index": 179,
      "start_time": 530429.0,
      "end_time": 533165.0,
      "text": "into a contract whereby I agree to transport"
    },
    {
      "index": 180,
      "start_time": 533165.0,
      "end_time": 536935.0,
      "text": "a shipment of laptop computers from your manufacturing plant"
    },
    {
      "index": 181,
      "start_time": 536936.0,
      "end_time": 539906.0,
      "text": "to your distributor across the country."
    },
    {
      "index": 182,
      "start_time": 539906.0,
      "end_time": 542808.0,
      "text": "If those laptops are damaged during shipping,"
    },
    {
      "index": 183,
      "start_time": 542808.0,
      "end_time": 545177.0,
      "text": "you might sue me for breach of contract."
    },
    {
      "index": 184,
      "start_time": 545177.0,
      "end_time": 547113.0,
      "text": "In adjudicating our dispute,"
    },
    {
      "index": 185,
      "start_time": 547113.0,
      "end_time": 550449.0,
      "text": "the court would look first to the contract between us."
    },
    {
      "index": 186,
      "start_time": 550449.0,
      "end_time": 552351.0,
      "text": "In our contract, we might have agreed"
    },
    {
      "index": 187,
      "start_time": 552351.0,
      "end_time": 555121.0,
      "text": "to a set of rules that differ from the default rules"
    },
    {
      "index": 188,
      "start_time": 555121.0,
      "end_time": 557689.0,
      "text": "found in the law of torts."
    },
    {
      "index": 189,
      "start_time": 557690.0,
      "end_time": 560393.0,
      "text": "This is known as \"contracting around"
    },
    {
      "index": 190,
      "start_time": 560393.0,
      "end_time": 562728.0,
      "text": "\"the tort law default rule.\""
    },
    {
      "index": 191,
      "start_time": 562728.0,
      "end_time": 565598.0,
      "text": "Alternatively, our contract might be silent"
    },
    {
      "index": 192,
      "start_time": 565598.0,
      "end_time": 567433.0,
      "text": "as to whether I am liable for damage"
    },
    {
      "index": 193,
      "start_time": 567433.0,
      "end_time": 569680.0,
      "text": "that occurs during shipping."
    },
    {
      "index": 194,
      "start_time": 569680.0,
      "end_time": 573472.0,
      "text": "In that case, the tort law default rules will apply."
    },
    {
      "index": 195,
      "start_time": 573472.0,
      "end_time": 576442.0,
      "text": "Note that a plaintiff can combine tort and contract"
    },
    {
      "index": 196,
      "start_time": 576442.0,
      "end_time": 579378.0,
      "text": "causes of action in a single civil suit."
    },
    {
      "index": 197,
      "start_time": 579378.0,
      "end_time": 582140.0,
      "text": "This often happens with regard to harms caused"
    },
    {
      "index": 198,
      "start_time": 582140.0,
      "end_time": 585151.0,
      "text": "by defective consumer products, for example."
    },
    {
      "index": 199,
      "start_time": 585151.0,
      "end_time": 587620.0,
      "text": "If I am injured by a defective blender"
    },
    {
      "index": 200,
      "start_time": 587620.0,
      "end_time": 590356.0,
      "text": "that you sold me, I might bring suit"
    },
    {
      "index": 201,
      "start_time": 590356.0,
      "end_time": 593859.0,
      "text": "for breach of warranty, a contract cause of action,"
    },
    {
      "index": 202,
      "start_time": 593859.0,
      "end_time": 596963.0,
      "text": "and for negligence, a tort cause of action."
    },
    {
      "index": 203,
      "start_time": 596963.0,
      "end_time": 598531.0,
      "text": "And you might be found liable"
    },
    {
      "index": 204,
      "start_time": 598531.0,
      "end_time": 601934.0,
      "text": "for neither, both, or either basis."
    },
    {
      "index": 205,
      "start_time": 601934.0,
      "end_time": 605137.0,
      "text": "So, a tort is a wrongful act,"
    },
    {
      "index": 206,
      "start_time": 605137.0,
      "end_time": 607600.0,
      "text": "other than a breach of contract,"
    },
    {
      "index": 207,
      "start_time": 607600.0,
      "end_time": 609574.0,
      "text": "that results in injury to another party&#39;s person,"
    },
    {
      "index": 208,
      "start_time": 609575.0,
      "end_time": 612378.0,
      "text": "property, dignity, or reputation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 209,
      "start_time": 612378.0,
      "end_time": 615448.0,
      "text": "and which is recognized by statute or common law"
    },
    {
      "index": 210,
      "start_time": 615448.0,
      "end_time": 617717.0,
      "text": "as a legitimate basis for liability."
    }
  ]
}